      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "Question Words",
        "content": "Essential interrogatives:\n                              \n   ✏️ Exercise: How do you ask 'Where is the book?'\n\n   ✏️ Exercise: ¿___ te llamas? (What is your name?)",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "¿Qué?",
            "english": "What?"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "¿Quién?",
            "english": "Who?"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "¿Cuándo?",
            "english": "When?"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "¿Dónde?",
            "english": "Where?"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "¿Por qué?",
            "english": "Why?"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "Negation",
        "content": "To make a sentence negative, put 'no' before the verb:\n            → Tengo hambre → No tengo hambre = I'm hungry → I'm not hungry",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "Hablo español → No hablo español",
            "english": "I speak Spanish → I don't speak Spanish"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "Tengo hambre → No tengo hambre",
            "english": "I'm hungry → I'm not hungry"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "Double Negatives",
        "content": "Unlike English, Spanish REQUIRES double negatives:\n                  → No voy nunca = I never go",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "No tengo nada",
            "english": "I don't have anything"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "No hay nadie",
            "english": "There isn't anyone"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "No voy nunca",
            "english": "I never go"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
